reduced.)  South Africa cut its winter wheat
forecast by 3.4 percent to 1.64 million metric tons, according
to Marda Scheepers, an official at the governmentâ€™s  Crop
Estimates Committee .  Farmers may reap 225,716 metric tons of malting barley, 5.6
percent less than earlier forecast, and 34,000 tons of canola,
19.1 percent less than previously estimated, she said by phone
